                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 1.  <span>Protocol for the generation of oligodendrocytes from NS cells.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>NS cells propagated in NS-A medium plus N2 in the presence of EGF and FGF2 (A) were cultured in DMEM/F12 plus N2 in the presence of FGF2, PDGF and forskolin for 4 days on polyornithine/laminin coated plastic (B) before they were induced to differentiate by growth factor withdrawal in the presence of 3,3,5-tri-iodothyronine hormone (T3) and ascorbic acid (AA) (C,D). After four days, immunostaining for the O4 antigen revealed differentiation into oligodendrocytes (C). The differentiated cultures also contained GFAP-positive astrocytes and ÃŸ-III tubulin/TUJ1-positive neurons (C,D), demonstrating the tripotential differentiation capacity of these cells.</p>
